<dd class='comment-body'>
<p>Les &#8211;<br /><br />You have to know that you are one of my favorite people.  I know you know this.  But I disagree with a lot of what you are saying here.  For one thing I just don&#8217;t see a violent response from anyone here in regards to defending Tolle.   There may be one exception with an anonymous comment but nothing here looks like blind loyalty.   There are a few of us who disagree with your assessment but &#8220;intense loyalty&#8221;??  Which particular comment would you be referring to when using the term &#8220;intense loyalty&#8221;?  I&#8217;m not trying to be a smartass.  I&#8217;m genuinely interested in knowing what gave you that impression. <br /><br />What I see here is a lot of knee-jerk reaction on the part of people who go into convulsions at the mention of the word &#8220;Oprah&#8221;; a lot of automatic dismissal of something almost purely because it&#8217;s gained some popularity.  You discount entirely the possibility that this is a hurting world, during a hurting time, and that suffering is causing a spiritual hunger in large numbers of people and here and there a teacher appears who can relate to the layperson and put timeless truths into ordinary and practical language.  (Not like us spiritual freaks who have been known to spend hours on end meditating and contemplating.) <br />   <br />Then there are the complaints about his delivery.  As far as I&#8217;m concerned that&#8217;s a completely subjective issue &#8211; different dispositions resonates with different styles of delivery.  You don&#8217;t like his delivery, fine.  I don&#8217;t really like Eddie Van Halen&#8217;s guitar playing but I can appreciate his talent.  Just not my style.  Give me Stevie Ray Vaughan any day.  <br /><br />You talk about how you can&#8217;t find anything on Tolle&#8217;s &#8220;organization&#8221;.  There&#8217;s a reason for that.  Because there is no organization!  <br /><br />I absolutely want to re-iterate that I could be way off base here.  I&#8217;m open to that possibility.  Prove me wrong.  Find some dirt on Tolle.  Find the angle.  If anyone can do it, you would be the guy.  But all this conjecture, talk about delivery, etc&#8230;this isn&#8217;t compelling.  You could literally say the same things about any spiritual teacher and find someone who would agree.  I have no problem with the fact that you don&#8217;t like Tolle for whatever reason.  But some of the claims, the hinting at something sinister, are just baseless (at least at this point).  <br /><br />Hoping you won&#8217;t interpret this to be a violent or caustic response on my part.  Honestly I think you like the pushback, otherwise you wouldn&#8217;t have done this.  <br /><br />(This comment thread is really something else. Wow!)<br /><br />Again, I have to mention that I have personally seen Tolle&#8217;s message have a transformative effect on a few people in my life; literally changes that I could visibly see on the person&#8217;s being, tears shed, old wounds healed, personal demons conquered, a measure of peace attained.   If that sounds like an exaggeration I&#8217;m sorry.  But I&#8217;ve seen it first hand.  I think the guy is waking people up.<br /><br />Jj -  If you happen to see this, would you mind sending me an email at bjd2222@hotmail.com?</p>
