<p>I think some people are confusing &quot;teacher&quot; with &quot;Guru.&quot; How many of you paid tuition at Stanford or Harvard? How much did you pay? Say again?  What did you learn about God, there? And how is that  education making you a better person?<br /><br />&quot;Understand this (above all); By surrender (of self-will) to the Guru, by (sensitive inward and outward) questioning (of the Guru), and by service (to the Guru), those (sages and Gurus) who have realized the truth will (be able to) convey their wisdom to you&quot; <br />Bhagavad Gita, 4:3<br /><br />Lot&#39;s of people have a &quot;money stress.&quot; They can&#39;t figure out it&#39;s energy (really, they can&#39;t handle it), so they turn against it and, any one who knows how to generate it, Whether the use of that money/energy is to uplift life or destroy life, it doesn&#39;t matter to them. The people with the money stress project onto those who don&#39;t. They WANT what they can&#39;t handle and turn against those who don&#39;t necessarily WANT but can handle it. That&#39;s why there are sooooooo many issues with having money and not having it...one of the BIG button pushers.<br /><br />At every moment, we as humans, are either damaging or supporting life that is so intimately ourselves...at every moment.</p>
