<p>I like Tolle. <br />His angle is similar to Buddha and pure Hinduism (as in the Bhagavad Gita) and is VERY difficult to understand since it says only the SPIRIT is real and that the &#39;MATERIAL WORLD&#39; is illusion. So<br />1) No need to despair watching the horrible stuff that is going on these days. Focus on the spirit and on projects that bring one closer to one&#39;s own spirit and to the spirit in others<br />2) That doesn&#39;t mean that one should not care about what is going on in the material world, one must do one&#39;s absolute best. But don&#39;t pin your happiness to whether your efforts in the material world are rewarded or not (&#39;karma yoga&#39;)</p>
